In Firefox (tested version: 22), the Filter Results Gadget has a blank space in the bottom depending on the size of the results returned. This by itself is harmless, but when I switch from one page to the next, the extra space disappears then immediately reappears, causing the screen contents to jump around. 

h3. Steps to Reproduce:
# Create over 20 issues with random Summaries;
# Create a filter returning those issues;
# Add the *Filter Results* gadget to the dashboard;
# Pass between the results (from 1-10 to 11-20 to 21-30 and so on).

h3. Expected Results:
The gadget's window would resize automatically to adjust to the size of the summaries returned.

h3. Actual Results:
The gadget does not correctly adjust the size automatically, which causes a blank space in the bottom of the gadget:
